Class Employee

java.lang.Object
  lab0.solution.Employee

public class Employee
extends java.lang.Object

In this challenge you need to address the probability that at some point the arguments to method parameters may not be valid.

For example, String arguments may be null or empty; other objects may be null; or primitive numbers may be out of acceptable range.

You need to validate ALL method parameters to make sure any and all arguments are valid. The only exception is when any argument is acceptable based on requirements. Fix the code below using if logic to validate method arguments and throw IllegalArgumentException or a custom exception if the validation fails.
